OL,3,CFour out of five teachers say new
OL,4,Cinspection system is needed
OL,6,FWatch: A survey suggests only 3% of
OL,7,Fteachers believe Ofsted acts as a
OL,8,F"reliable and trusted arbiter of
OL,9,Fstandards". ITV News' Social Affairs
OL,10,FCorrespondent Stacey Foster has more
OL,12,FMore than four out of five teachers in
OL,13,FEngland believe a new system of
OL,14,Finspection should be introduced
OL,15,Fbecause Ofsted has "many problems", a
OL,16,Fsurvey suggests.
OL,18,FThe majority of teachers (90%) said
OL,19,Fthey do not believe single-word
OL,20,Fjudgments are a fair reflection of the
OL,21,Fperformance of a school.
