OL,6,F"Single-word judgments are destructive
OL,7,Fand wrong, and our members agree. But
OL,8,Fthe faults of Ofsted run much deeper.
OL,9,FThere are serious wellbeing concerns,
OL,10,Fbrought to stark public attention last
OL,11,Fyear."
OL,13,F"We know that Ofsted has been forced
OL,14,Finto a listening exercise because of
OL,15,Fthat tragedy, but the NEU and its
OL,16,Fmembership do not believe this will
OL,17,Flead to fundamental change."
OL,19,FMr Kebede added, "Only root-and-branch
OL,20,Freform can bring an end to the tyranny
OL,21,Fof inspection."
